    question: "Aurora Corp. reports EBIT of $5 million, depreciation of $1.2 million, capital expenditures of $800,000, change in net working capital of $300,000, and a tax rate of 25%. What is the free cash flow to the firm (FCFF)?",
    options: ["$4,950,000","$4,850,000","$3,850,000","$5,150,000"],
    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "FCFF = EBIT × (1 − Tax Rate) + Depreciation − CapEx − Change in NWC. FCFF = $5,000,000 × (1 − 0.25) + $1,200,000 − $800,000 − $300,000 = $3,750,000 + $1,200,000 − $800,000 − $300,000 = $3,850,000. FCFF represents cash available to all capital providers (debt and equity) before financing costs.",
