    educational: "In consolidated financial statements, intercompany transactions must be eliminated to present the financial position and results of operations as if the group were a single entity. This prevents overstating assets and income due to internal transactions that haven't been realized with external parties. The unrealized profit is the profit embedded in the inventory still held within the consolidated group.",
    examTip: "Always focus on the percentage of inventory *remaining* when calculating unrealized profit in intercompany transactions; the sold portion is already realized.",
    memoryAid: "Unsold = Unrealized = Eliminate",
