      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - The Internal Rate of Return (IRR) represents the discount rate at which the project's net present value (NPV) equals zero. If the IRR exceeds the hurdle rate (the minimum acceptable rate of return), the project is expected to be profitable and should be accepted.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - While it's true the payback period doesn't consider the time value of money, this fact doesn't automatically lead to project rejection when other methods, like IRR, suggest acceptance.",
