    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Treasury stock method for diluted EPS: (1) Assume all dilutive options/warrants are exercised at the beginning of the period (or grant date if later), (2) Assume the entity receives the exercise price, (3) Use those proceeds to buy back shares at the average market price for the period, (4) The difference (shares issued − shares repurchased) represents the incremental dilutive shares added to the denominator. Options are dilutive only when the exercise price < average market price (in the money). If exercise price > average market price (out of the money), the options are antidilutive and excluded from diluted EPS. The numerator is NOT adjusted under the treasury stock method.",
