    examTip: "When assessing VIE status, carefully analyze the equity holders' rights and obligations; look for indicators of insufficient equity at risk, limited decision-making power, or disproportionate risk/reward allocation.",
    memoryAid: "DER: Decision-making, Equity at risk, Residual returns/losses. If any of these are lacking, it might be a VIE.",
    reference: "ASC 810-10-15 — Variable Interest Entities",
