    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 842 provides a practical expedient: Leases with a term of 12 months or less at commencement (and no purchase option reasonably certain to be exercised) may be excluded from balance sheet recognition. The lessee recognizes lease expense on a straight-line basis over the lease term. The election is made by asset class (must be applied consistently). A lease that contains a renewal option is NOT short-term if the lessee is reasonably certain to exercise the renewal, causing the total term to exceed 12 months. Note: IFRS 16 also provides a low-value asset exemption (not in US GAAP).",
