    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 280 uses a management approach: segments are identified based on how the entity is organized and evaluated internally by the CODM. The CODM is a function (not necessarily a specific title) — it could be the CEO, COO, or a group of executives who make key resource allocation decisions. An operating segment must: (1) engage in business activities that may earn revenues and incur expenses, (2) have operating results regularly reviewed by the CODM, and (3) have discrete financial information available. Segmentation may be by product lines, geographic areas, customer types, or any other basis used internally. This aligns external reporting with internal management reporting.",
