    question: "Under ASC 205-20, a component of an entity is reported as a discontinued operation if:",
    options: ["The component is no longer generating positive cash flows","The component has been disposed of or meets the criteria to be classified as held for sale AND the disposal represents a strategic shift that has (or will have) a major effect on the entity's operations and financial results","The component operated at a loss for two consecutive quarters","Management decides to restructure the component"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 205-20 criteria for discontinued operations (as amended by ASU 2014-08): The component must be (1) disposed of (or meet held-for-sale criteria), AND (2) the disposal must represent a strategic shift that has (or will have) a major effect on the entity's operations and financial results. Examples of strategic shifts: disposal of a major geographic area, a major line of business, a major equity method investment, or other major parts of an entity. Presentation: results of discontinued operations are reported separately (after income from continuing operations, net of tax). Assets and liabilities of held-for-sale disposal groups are presented separately on the balance sheet. The strategic shift requirement raised the bar from prior guidance, reducing the frequency of discontinued operations reporting.",
