      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Operating at a loss for two consecutive quarters is a performance indicator, but it doesn't automatically trigger discontinued operations reporting. The strategic shift criterion is crucial.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Management's decision to restructure a component, by itself, doesn't qualify it as a discontinued operation. A disposal (or held-for-sale classification) and a strategic shift are required.",
