      2: "Why option C is WRONG - This answer is incorrect and doesn't represent any standard financial ratio calculation using the provided figures.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - This answer represents the Equity Multiplier (Total Assets / Total Equity), not the Debt-to-Equity ratio. It uses the total assets figure, which needs to be calculated (Liabilities + Equity = Assets).",
