      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - Level 1 inputs are the most reliable because they are based on actual transactions for identical assets or liabilities in active markets, providing the most direct evidence of fair value.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Observable inputs other than quoted prices, such as interest rates and yield curves, are classified as Level 2 inputs, not Level 1.",
