    educational: "Transfer pricing involves setting prices for goods, services, or intellectual property transferred between related entities within a multinational corporation. By manipulating these prices, companies can artificially inflate profits in low-tax countries and reduce them in high-tax countries, thereby minimizing their overall tax obligations. This practice is closely scrutinized by tax authorities worldwide.",
