    explanation: "Cash flow hedge accounting under ASC 815-30: the effective portion of the derivative's gain/loss goes to OCI (Accumulated Other Comprehensive Income on the balance sheet). It is reclassified from AOCI to earnings in the same period(s) that the hedged forecasted transaction affects earnings. The ineffective portion is recognized in earnings immediately. Common cash flow hedges: hedging forecasted purchases (commodity price risk), forecasted foreign currency sales, variable rate interest payments. Documentation and effectiveness testing requirements must be met.",
