    educational: "The inventory turnover ratio measures how efficiently a company is managing its inventory. A higher turnover generally suggests strong sales and effective inventory management, while a lower turnover might indicate overstocking or slow sales. Analyzing this ratio helps assess a company's operational efficiency and liquidity.",
    examTip: "Remember the inventory turnover formula: COGS over Average Inventory; think 'Cost Over Average'.",
    memoryAid: "COGS over Average Inventory = Turnover (CAT)",
