    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 718 requires the fair value method. Fair value is estimated at the grant date using an option-pricing model (Black-Scholes or binomial/lattice). Compensation expense = Fair value × Number of options expected to vest. Expense is recognized straight-line over the vesting period. Journal entry each period: Dr. Compensation Expense, Cr. Additional Paid-In Capital (equity). If options expire unexercised, no reversal of previously recognized expense. Upon exercise: APIC is reclassified.",
