      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Assigning a value of zero until exercise ignores the economic benefit conferred to the employee at the grant date. ASC 718 requires recognition of this benefit over the service period, not waiting until exercise.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While intrinsic value (stock price minus exercise price) can be a component of fair value, it's not the only factor. Option-pricing models consider factors like volatility and time to expiration, which are ignored by intrinsic value alone.",
