    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "ASC 842 finance lease criteria (any one): (1) Transfer of ownership at lease end, (2) Purchase option reasonably certain to be exercised, (3) Lease term ≥ major part (75%) of economic life, (4) PV of lease payments ≥ substantially all (90%) of fair value, (5) Asset is specialized with no alternative use to lessor. Under ASC 842, ALL leases > 12 months are on the balance sheet (ROU asset + lease liability). Finance leases have front-loaded expense (interest + amortization); operating leases have straight-line expense.",
