    correctAnswer: 0,
    explanation: "ASC 830 translation methods depend on functional currency: (1) Functional = local currency → current rate method: B/S at current rate (except equity at historical), I/S at average rate; translation adjustment in OCI (CTA — Cumulative Translation Adjustment). (2) Functional = parent's currency → temporal (remeasurement) method: monetary items at current rate, non-monetary items at historical rate; remeasurement gain/loss in net income. Key distinction: translation (CTA in OCI) vs. remeasurement (gain/loss in income).",
