      1: "Option B is WRONG because the forward exchange rate is not used to translate all financial statement items under either the current rate or temporal methods. The forward rate is primarily used in hedging transactions.",
      2: "Option C is WRONG because using the historical exchange rate for all items is not consistent with either the current rate or temporal methods. The historical rate is only used for specific items, such as equity accounts under the current rate method or non-monetary assets under the temporal method.",
