    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Times Interest Earned (TIE) = EBIT / Interest Expense = $450,000 / $90,000 = 5.0 times. This means the company earns five times its required interest payments. Generally, a TIE above 3.0 indicates comfortable debt service capacity. Lenders frequently require minimum TIE covenants in loan agreements.",
