    educational: "Cost variances help management control costs by highlighting deviations from planned performance. Analyzing these variances allows for corrective actions and improved future budgeting. Understanding the individual components of variances, like price and quantity, is crucial for effective cost management.",
    examTip: "Carefully distinguish between price and quantity variances; price variances focus on the cost per unit, while quantity variances focus on the amount used.",
    memoryAid: "MPV = (AP-SP)AQ: Materials Price Variance equals (Actual Price minus Standard Price) times Actual Quantity purchased.",
