    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ROE = Net Income ÷ Average Total Equity = $150,000 ÷ $1,000,000 = 15%. ROE measures the return generated on shareholders' investment. It can be decomposed using the DuPont formula: ROE = Profit Margin × Asset Turnover × Equity Multiplier = (NI ÷ Sales) × (Sales ÷ Average Total Assets) × (Average Total Assets ÷ Average Equity). This decomposition identifies whether ROE is driven by profitability, asset efficiency, or financial leverage. A higher ROE is generally better, but must be evaluated considering the level of risk (leverage).",
