    educational: "The Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC) represents the minimum rate of return a company must earn on its existing asset base to satisfy its creditors, investors, and owners. It's a crucial metric for investment decisions, as projects with expected returns exceeding the WACC are generally considered value-creating.",
    examTip: "Always remember to calculate the after-tax cost of debt before calculating WACC; failing to do so is a common mistake.",
