    explanation: "Cash conversion cycle = DIO + DSO − DPO = 45 + 30 − 25 = 50 days. The CCC measures the time (in days) between paying suppliers for raw materials and collecting cash from customers. A shorter CCC means the company converts its investments in inventory and receivables into cash more quickly. Strategies to reduce CCC: (1) reduce DIO by improving inventory management, (2) reduce DSO by accelerating collections, (3) increase DPO by negotiating longer payment terms with suppliers. A negative CCC (rare) means the company collects from customers before paying suppliers (e.g., some retailers).",
