    educational: "The cash conversion cycle (CCC) is a vital metric for assessing a company's liquidity and operational efficiency. A shorter CCC indicates that a company is efficiently managing its working capital, minimizing the time its cash is tied up in inventory and receivables. Improving the CCC can free up cash for other investments or reduce the need for external financing.",
    examTip: "Double-check the formula for CCC (DIO + DSO - DPO) and ensure you're subtracting DPO, as it represents a delay in cash outflow, not inflow.",
