    options: ["7,500 units","8,500 units","10,000 units","6,000 units"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Production budget: Units to produce = Budgeted sales + Desired ending inventory − Beginning inventory = 8,000 + 2,000 − 1,500 = 8,500 units. This formula ensures the company will have enough units to meet sales demand while building inventory to the desired ending level. The production budget flows into direct materials, direct labor, and overhead budgets. If ending inventory is desired to be higher than beginning inventory (as here, 2,000 vs. 1,500), production must exceed sales. The 500-unit inventory build-up requires producing 500 more units than planned sales.",
