      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Revenue growth and asset growth are indicators of expansion, but they don't directly calculate ROI. While growth can contribute to higher ROI, it's not a direct component of the DuPont formula.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Operating income divided by fixed assets is a measure of fixed asset turnover or utilization, but it doesn't represent the complete picture of ROI. ROI considers all invested capital, not just fixed assets.",
