    educational: "The DuPont formula breaks down ROI into its core components: profitability (margin) and efficiency (turnover). A high margin indicates strong pricing power or cost control, while a high turnover suggests efficient asset utilization. Understanding these drivers allows managers to pinpoint areas for improvement and optimize divisional performance.",
    examTip: "Remember the DuPont formula: ROI = Margin x Turnover; if you're stuck, think 'Profitability times Efficiency'.",
