    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "EVA = NOPAT − (WACC × Invested capital), where NOPAT = Net Operating Profit After Tax. Key adjustments that differentiate EVA from simple residual income: (1) capitalize and amortize R&D instead of expensing, (2) add back goodwill amortization, (3) capitalize operating leases, (4) use beginning-of-period capital, (5) remove non-cash charges. These adjustments aim to convert accounting income into economic profit. Positive EVA indicates value creation; negative EVA indicates value destruction. Created by Stern Stewart & Co., EVA has become a widely used performance metric that aligns management behavior with shareholder wealth maximization.",
