    educational: "Responsibility accounting divides an organization into segments where managers are held accountable for specific financial results. The level of responsibility assigned dictates the type of center: cost, revenue, profit, or investment. Understanding these distinctions is crucial for performance evaluation and incentivizing desired behaviors.",
