    explanation: "COSO ERM (2017 update): Enterprise Risk Management—Integrating with Strategy and Performance. Five components: (1) Governance and Culture, (2) Strategy and Objective-Setting, (3) Performance (identifying, assessing, prioritizing risks), (4) Review and Revision (monitoring), (5) Information, Communication, and Reporting. ERM is holistic (enterprise-wide, not siloed), proactive, integrated with strategy, and considers risk appetite — the amount and type of risk an organization is willing to accept in pursuit of value. ERM does not aim to eliminate risk but to manage it within acceptable levels. Risk responses: accept, avoid, reduce, share/transfer.",
