    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "ASC 805 (Business Combinations) — the acquisition method: (1) Identify the acquirer, (2) Determine the acquisition date, (3) Recognize and measure identifiable assets acquired and liabilities assumed at fair value, (4) Recognize goodwill or a bargain purchase gain. Goodwill = Consideration paid + NCI fair value + Previously held equity interest fair value − Fair value of identifiable net assets acquired. If consideration < fair value of net assets, a bargain purchase gain is recognized in earnings. Acquisition costs (legal, advisory, due diligence) are expensed as incurred, not capitalized. Pooling of interests was eliminated by SFAS 141/ASC 805.",
