      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Arranging for another party to provide the good or service is the role of an agent, not a principal. Agents do not control the good or service before it is transferred to the customer.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Receiving a commission is characteristic of an agent. Principals derive revenue from the sale of the good or service itself, not just a commission.",
