      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - The measurement period allows for adjustments to provisional amounts recognized in a business combination for up to one year as the acquirer obtains new information about facts and circumstances that existed at the acquisition date. This ensures that the acquirer has sufficient time to gather and analyze information for accurate valuation.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Immediate finalization is not required because ASC 805 recognizes that obtaining complete information for valuation can take time; a measurement period is provided for this reason.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - The measurement period is a defined period of up to one year, not the life of the acquired assets; after this period, subsequent changes are recognized in earnings, not as adjustments to the initial acquisition accounting.",
