    educational: "In a business combination, it's often impossible to determine the fair values of assets and liabilities immediately. The measurement period exists to allow the acquirer a reasonable amount of time to obtain the necessary information to finalize these values. This period ensures more accurate and reliable financial reporting.",
    examTip: "Focus on the one-year limit of the measurement period and remember that adjustments are made retrospectively as if the information was known on the acquisition date.",
    memoryAid: "One Year to Measure (OYM): Remember the measurement period is capped at *one year*.",
