    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "The three levers to improve EVA are: increase NOPAT, reduce WACC, or reduce invested capital. Since NOPAT ($1M) and WACC (12.5%) stayed constant while invested capital decreased from $12M to $8M, the improvement came from capital efficiency — divesting underperforming assets. Year 1 EVA = $1M − ($12M × 12.5%) = $1M − $1.5M = −$500K. Year 2 EVA = $1M − ($8M × 12.5%) = $1M − $1M = $0. The actual improvement to $200K suggests slightly higher NOPAT or lower capital.",
