    question: "Blackwell Corp. uses the LIFO method for inventory valuation. It has inventory with a LIFO cost of $280,000, replacement cost of $250,000, net realizable value of $310,000, and NRV less normal profit margin of $265,000. Under ASC 330, what amount should Blackwell report for this inventory?",
    options: ["$310,000","$280,000","$265,000","$250,000"],
    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "For LIFO and retail method entities, ASC 330-10-35-1A still uses the traditional lower-of-cost-or-market rule (not the simplified NRV approach). Market = replacement cost ($250,000), but capped at NRV ceiling ($310,000) and floored at NRV less normal profit margin ($265,000). Since $250,000 < $265,000 floor, market = $265,000. Then LCM = lower of cost ($280,000) or market ($265,000) = $265,000.",
