    educational: "Goodwill represents the excess of the purchase price of an acquired business over the fair value of its identifiable net assets. Because goodwill's value is tied to the overall business, it's tested for impairment at the reporting unit level, ensuring that any decline in the unit's value is reflected in the financial statements.",
    examTip: "Remember that goodwill impairment testing involves comparing the fair value of the reporting unit to its carrying amount; focus on this comparison to answer goodwill impairment questions correctly.",
