    skillLevel: "Analysis",
    question: "The Projected Benefit Obligation (PBO) is increased by:",
    options: ["Service cost and interest cost","Benefits paid to retirees","Actual return on plan assets","Contributions to the plan"],
    correctAnswer: 0,
    explanation: "PBO is increased by service cost (benefits earned this period) and interest cost (time value increase). It is decreased by benefits paid and actuarial gains. Plan assets are separate from PBO.",
