      1: "Why option B is WRONG - Benefits paid to retirees decrease the PBO because the company is fulfilling its obligation by paying out those benefits, thereby reducing the remaining future obligation.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Actual return on plan assets affects the funded status of the pension plan (the difference between plan assets and PBO), but it does not directly impact the PBO itself. Plan assets and PBO are distinct components of pension accounting.",
