      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - When a foreign subsidiary operates in a highly inflationary environment, the parent company's reporting currency is used as the functional currency. This requires remeasurement using the temporal method, with any resulting gains or losses recognized in current income, preventing significant and misleading cumulative translation adjustments (CTA).",
