    question: "Paragon Corp. discovers in Q3 that its annual effective tax rate should be 28% instead of the originally estimated 25%. Through Q2, Paragon recognized $500,000 of income tax expense on $2,000,000 of pre-tax income. Q3 pre-tax income is $800,000. What is the Q3 income tax expense?",
    options: ["$224,000","$284,000","$200,000","$340,000"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Under ASC 270-10-45 (integral approach), each quarter uses the estimated annual effective tax rate (EAETR). Cumulative tax through Q3 = ($2,000,000 + $800,000) × 28% = $784,000. Tax already recognized through Q2 = $500,000. Q3 tax expense = $784,000 − $500,000 = $284,000. The change in estimated rate creates a catch-up in Q3.",
