    options: ["51,000","45,000","44,000","60,000"],
    correctAnswer: 2,
    explanation: "FIFO equivalent units calculation: (1) Complete beginning WIP: 10,000 × (100% - 40%) = 6,000 units. (2) Started and completed: 45,000 - 10,000 = 35,000 units. (3) Ending WIP: 15,000 × 20% = 3,000 units. Total EU = 6,000 + 35,000 + 3,000 = 44,000. Under FIFO, only the work done in the current period is counted, so beginning WIP gets credit only for the remaining 60% completion, and ending WIP is 20% complete for conversion.",
