      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - The Net Present Value (NPV) is calculated by discounting all future cash flows to their present value and subtracting the initial investment. In this case, the present value of the cash inflows is $35,000 * 3.170 = $110,950. Subtracting the $100,000 initial investment results in an NPV of $10,950.",
