      2: "Why option C is CORRECT - The perpetuity growth model (TV = FCF × (1+g)/(r-g)) requires the discount rate (r) to be higher than the growth rate (g). If 'g' exceeds 'r', the denominator becomes negative or zero, resulting in an undefined or nonsensical terminal value.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - While long-term growth often approximates inflation, inflation itself isn't the limiting factor in the perpetuity growth model formula; the discount rate is.",
