      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Capitalizing software costs doesn't automatically improve earnings quality; it depends on whether it accurately reflects the economic reality and is consistently applied. Aggressive capitalization, especially when peers expense similar costs, can distort earnings and lower earnings quality.",
      3: "Why option D is WRONG - Bad debt provisions are estimates, but they significantly impact earnings quality. Under-provisioning inflates both revenues and assets, creating a misleading picture of the company's financial health and potentially masking underlying credit risks.",
