    explanation: "Horizontal analysis (also called trend analysis) compares each line item across time periods by expressing current-period amounts as a percentage of the corresponding base-period amount. This differs from vertical analysis, which expresses items as a percentage of a base amount within the same period (e.g., total assets or total revenue).",
