      1: "Why option B is CORRECT - ASC 606 provides two methods for estimating variable consideration: the expected value (sum of probability-weighted amounts) and the most likely amount. The entity selects the method that best predicts the amount of revenue to which it is entitled.",
      2: "Why option C is WRONG - Fair market value is used for valuing assets and liabilities, particularly in business combinations or when determining impairment, not for estimating variable consideration in revenue recognition.",
