    educational: "The labor efficiency variance measures how well labor hours are utilized. A favorable variance suggests that less labor time was needed than anticipated based on the standard, indicating efficient operations. Conversely, an unfavorable variance means more labor time was used than expected, suggesting inefficiencies.",
