    options: ["Division Beta, because its higher variable cost ratio erodes margins faster","Division Alpha, because its higher DOL causes operating income to fall by a greater percentage","Both are equally affected because they have the same total costs at $8M revenue","Division Alpha, but only because it has higher absolute fixed costs"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "Alpha: CM = $8M × 50% = $4M, OI = $4M − $4M = $0 (breakeven). Beta: CM = $8M × 25% = $2M, OI = $2M − $1.5M = $500K. Alpha's DOL is undefined (at breakeven), meaning any revenue decline causes losses. Beta's DOL = $2M/$500K = 4.0. Alpha has greater downside risk because it operates at breakeven with high fixed costs—any revenue decline immediately produces losses.",
