      1: "This answer incorrectly calculates goodwill, likely by omitting the fair value of the noncontrolling interest or miscalculating the total consideration paid.",
      2: "A bargain purchase exists when the consideration transferred plus the NCI fair value is *less* than the fair value of identifiable net assets acquired; here, it is more, indicating goodwill, not a gain.",
