      3: "Why option D is CORRECT - For a cash flow hedge, the effective portion of the derivative's gain or loss is initially reported in Other Comprehensive Income (OCI). It is then reclassified out of OCI and into earnings in the same period(s) during which the hedged transaction affects earnings (when the inventory is sold and impacts cost of goods sold).",
