    question: "Apex Corporation sells two products: Alpha and Beta. Alpha sells for $50 per unit and has variable costs of $30 per unit. Beta sells for $80 per unit and has variable costs of $40 per unit. Apex's fixed costs are $600,000. Apex sells twice as many units of Alpha as Beta. What is the break-even point in units for Beta?",
