    educational: "Variance analysis helps management identify deviations from planned performance. The materials price variance specifically isolates the impact of price differences between actual and standard costs of materials purchased. A positive variance (actual > standard) is unfavorable, while a negative variance (actual < standard) is favorable.",
    examTip: "Remember the formula: (Actual Price - Standard Price) * Actual Quantity. Pay close attention to whether the variance is favorable or unfavorable based on whether the actual price is lower or higher than the standard price.",
    memoryAid: "APAQ: Actual Price - Actual Price * Quantity",
