    options: ["Management must disclose the loss of the customer in the subsequent events footnote but does not need to explicitly evaluate going concern since the event occurred after year-end.","Management must evaluate whether the conditions and events, considered in the aggregate, raise substantial doubt about the entity’s ability to continue as a going concern within one year after the date that the financial statements are issued.","Management is only required to disclose the new customer contract negotiation in the subsequent events footnote if the contract is finalized before the 10-K filing date.","Management is not required to disclose anything about the loss of the customer or the going concern assessment in the 10-K filing because the auditor is responsible for the going concern opinion."],
