    question: "GlobalTech, a U.S.-based company, has a wholly-owned subsidiary, EuroSubsidiary, operating in France. EuroSubsidiary's transactions are primarily conducted in Euros. The subsidiary's sales are primarily to customers in France and other European countries. The subsidiary's labor, materials, and other production costs are also primarily denominated in Euros. EuroSubsidiary takes out a loan denominated in Euros from a local French bank. However, EuroSubsidiary remits all of its cash flows back to GlobalTech in U.S. Dollars on a monthly basis. Based on this information, what is EuroSubsidiary's functional currency?",
    options: ["U.S. Dollar","Euro","A weighted average of the U.S. Dollar and Euro","The currency of the country with the largest customer base for EuroSubsidiary"],
