    educational: "Functional currency is determined by evaluating various economic factors, including cash flow indicators, sales market indicators, expense indicators, financing indicators, and intercompany transactions. The goal is to identify the currency that best reflects the economic environment in which the entity primarily generates and expends cash.",
    examTip: "Be careful not to overemphasize one factor, such as intercompany transactions. Consider all indicators to determine the functional currency.",
    memoryAid: "Cash Flow, Sales, Expenses, Financing (CSEF) - remember these factors when determining functional currency.",
    reference: "ASC 830",
