    options: ["Disclose the principal conditions that raise substantial doubt about its ability to continue as a going concern, management's evaluation of the significance of those conditions, and management's plans that alleviate substantial doubt.","Obtain written guarantees from major creditors assuring continued lines of credit for at least one year after the date of the financial statements.","Engage an independent valuation specialist to prepare a liquidation analysis demonstrating the net realizable value of the company's assets exceeds its liabilities.","Restate prior period financial statements to reflect the company's likely liquidation value."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
