    question: "ABC Corp. is preparing its financial statements for the year ended December 31, 2023. Due to a significant downturn in the economy and a major product recall, ABC Corp. has experienced substantial operating losses and is facing liquidity challenges. Management has prepared a going concern assessment as of the date the financial statements are issued, March 15, 2024. Based on management's assessment, substantial doubt about ABC Corp.'s ability to continue as a going concern exists. Which of the following disclosures is *not* required in ABC Corp.'s 2023 financial statements?",
