    question: "Crestwood Manufacturing, a publicly traded company, recently implemented a new Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system. To ensure the effectiveness of internal controls related to financial reporting within the new system, which of the following monitoring activities would be MOST effective in identifying and addressing potential control deficiencies in a timely manner?",
    options: ["A comprehensive annual audit of the ERP system's security features by an external cybersecurity firm.","Periodic self-assessments by department managers, focusing solely on the controls within their respective departments and reporting findings to the CFO.","Ongoing monitoring of key performance indicators (KPIs) and data analytics focusing on transaction processing and unusual patterns, coupled with regular management review and follow-up on identified exceptions.","Relying primarily on user feedback and incident reports submitted through the IT help desk, with occasional spot checks by the internal audit department."],
