    question: "Apex Corporation's internal audit department discovered that several key controls over financial reporting were not operating effectively during the first quarter. Management implemented corrective actions immediately and believes the issue is resolved. According to the COSO framework, what is the MOST appropriate next step for Apex regarding monitoring activities?",
    options: ["A. No further action is required, as the corrective actions have been implemented.","B. The internal audit department should perform a separate evaluation to verify the effectiveness of the corrective actions.","C. Management should document the control deficiency in the subsequent quarterly report to shareholders.","D. Management should rely on self-assessment by the personnel responsible for the ineffective controls to ensure they are now operating effectively."],
