    options: ["Develop a contingency plan to quickly switch to an alternative supplier, even if it results in slightly higher costs and a potential delay of 1-2 months.","Negotiate a prepayment arrangement with SolarParts Inc. to ensure they have sufficient capital to continue production, accepting the risk of potential loss of prepayment if SolarParts declares bankruptcy.","Purchase credit default swaps (CDS) on SolarParts Inc.'s debt, hedging against the risk of default but without addressing the supply chain disruption.","Ignore the risk, as SolarParts has been a reliable supplier in the past and these 'financial difficulties' are likely temporary."],
