    question: "Tech Solutions Inc. is evaluating its performance measurement system. The company implemented a new customer relationship management (CRM) system at the beginning of the year, aiming to improve customer satisfaction and retention. Key performance indicators (KPIs) related to customer service include:\n\n*   Average call resolution time\n*   Customer satisfaction score (measured through surveys)\n*   Number of new customer acquisitions\n\nDuring the year, the average call resolution time increased by 15%, the customer satisfaction score decreased by 10%, and the number of new customer acquisitions increased by 20%. Senior management is concerned about the conflicting signals from these KPIs. Which of the following actions is MOST appropriate for Tech Solutions Inc. to take?",
    options: ["Discontinue the use of the CRM system since it is not improving customer satisfaction.","Investigate the reasons for the increase in call resolution time and the decrease in customer satisfaction score while considering the impact of the new customer acquisitions.","Focus solely on the increase in new customer acquisitions as the primary indicator of success.","Ignore the customer satisfaction score since it is subjective and not a reliable measure of performance."],
