    question: "Alpha Corp. plans to acquire Beta Inc. in an all-stock transaction. Alpha has 1,000,000 shares of common stock outstanding, with a market price of $50 per share. Beta has 500,000 shares of common stock outstanding, with a market price of $20 per share. The acquisition is expected to increase Alpha's net income by $2,000,000 annually. Alpha will issue new shares to Beta's shareholders based on the relative market values of the two companies. What is the pro forma earnings per share (EPS) of the combined entity, assuming Alpha's current net income is $10,000,000?",
    options: ["$8.00","$9.00","$10.00","$12.00"],
