    explanation: "Reviewing system access logs provides direct evidence of whether access controls are working as intended and whether any unauthorized access attempts are occurring. The investigation and resolution of incidents demonstrate a proactive approach to addressing control deficiencies. This is a direct and ongoing monitoring activity providing persuasive evidence of the control's effectiveness. (COSO Framework)",
