    question: "Baker Company has the following information available for the year ended December 31, 2024:\n\n*   Cash: $50,000\n*   Accounts Receivable: $100,000\n*   Inventory: $150,000\n*   Accounts Payable: $80,000\n*   Salaries Payable: $20,000\n*   Prepaid Insurance: $10,000\n\nWhat is Baker Company's quick ratio?",
    options: ["1.50","1.60","1.75","3.10"],
    correctAnswer: 1,
    explanation: "The quick ratio (also known as the acid-test ratio) is calculated as (Cash + Accounts Receivable + Marketable Securities) / Current Liabilities. In this case, it's ($50,000 + $100,000 + $10,000) / ($80,000 + $20,000) = $160,000 / $100,000 = 1.60.",
