    educational: "Break-even analysis determines the sales level needed to cover all costs. The break-even point is where total revenue equals total costs (fixed + variable). Understanding contribution margin (sales price less variable costs) is crucial for break-even calculations.",
    examTip: "Always remember to use contribution margin (selling price - variable costs) in break-even calculations. Carefully distinguish between break-even in units and break-even in dollars.",
    memoryAid: "BEU (Break-Even Units) = FC (Fixed Costs) / CMpu (Contribution Margin per unit)",
    reference: "AICPA Guide Prospective Financial Information",
