    question: "Apex Corp. has experienced declining profitability and is nearing covenant default on its long-term debt. Apex is considering strategies to improve its debt-to-equity ratio. Which of the following actions would most likely improve Apex Corp.'s debt-to-equity ratio in the short term?",
    options: ["Issue new common stock for cash and use the proceeds to pay down existing accounts payable.","Sell a division for cash and use the proceeds to pay down a portion of its long-term debt.","Refinance short-term debt with new long-term debt at a lower interest rate.","Increase sales through more aggressive credit terms, increasing accounts receivable and decreasing inventory."],
