    educational: "Variance analysis identifies deviations from planned performance, helping management pinpoint areas needing attention. A key part of variance analysis is determining the materiality threshold - the level at which a variance becomes significant enough to warrant investigation. Companies set policies to investigate only material variances to efficiently use their resources.",
    examTip: "Always read the company's policy on variance investigation carefully. The policy may specify whether individual variances or net variances are used for materiality assessment. Pay attention to whether the variance is favorable or unfavorable, and the wording of the question.",
    memoryAid: "Net Unfavorable = Unfavorable - Favorable",
    reference: "COSO Framework",
