    question: "Apex Manufacturing uses a standard cost system. The standard cost for one unit of their primary product, the Widget, includes 2 direct labor hours at a rate of $25 per hour. During July, Apex produced 5,000 Widgets. Actual direct labor costs were $275,000 for 10,500 direct labor hours. What is the flexible budget variance for direct labor?",
