    question: "Apex Manufacturing is implementing a new Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system. As part of the implementation, the company plans to rely heavily on automated controls within the system to monitor transaction processing. Senior management has decided to significantly reduce the internal audit staff to offset the ERP system's cost. Which of the following statements best describes the potential impact on Apex's internal control system?",
    options: ["A reduction in internal audit staff, coupled with reliance on automated controls, inherently weakens the control environment and significantly increases the risk of material misstatement.","Relying on automated controls eliminates the need for a robust internal audit function as the ERP system provides real-time monitoring of transactions.","A reduction in internal audit staff is acceptable if the automated controls within the ERP system are properly designed and tested, and if management implements effective monitoring activities to oversee the system's performance.","The reduction in internal audit staff will have no impact on the internal control system as long as the company continues to perform monthly bank reconciliations."],
