    options: ["Establish a decentralized risk management structure, delegating responsibility to individual business units in each country to allow for localized expertise.","Conduct a comprehensive risk assessment across all international operations, focusing on identifying and prioritizing key risks related to each market's specific environment.","Reduce the overall budget allocated to risk management to minimize overhead costs associated with international expansion.","Rely solely on external consultants to manage risks in new markets, as they possess specialized expertise in international regulations and compliance."],
