    educational: "The times interest earned ratio indicates a company's ability to cover its interest expense with its earnings. A higher ratio suggests a greater ability to meet interest obligations, indicating stronger solvency.",
    examTip: "Remember the formula: Times Interest Earned = EBIT / Interest Expense. Focus on correctly calculating EBIT from the information provided.",
    memoryAid: "TIE = Earnings Before Interest and Taxes / Interest Expense (TIE ratio helps tie earnings to interest obligations)",
    reference: "Financial Accounting and Analysis textbook",
