    examTip: "Always double-check whether the problem asks for a favorable or unfavorable variance. A higher actual price compared to the standard price always results in an unfavorable variance.",
    memoryAid: "Price Variance = (Actual Price - Standard Price) * Actual Quantity. Think 'AP-SP' then multiply by 'AQ'.",
    reference: "Cost Accounting Principles and Practices",
