    question: "Apex Manufacturing uses a standard costing system. The company's policy is to investigate all variances exceeding $5,000 or 10% of the budgeted amount, whichever is larger. For the current month, the following data pertains to direct labor:\n\nBudgeted direct labor cost: $40,000\nActual direct labor cost: $43,500\n\nBased on this information, should Apex investigate the direct labor variance?",
    options: ["No, because the variance is less than both the dollar and percentage thresholds.","Yes, because the variance exceeds the dollar threshold.","Yes, because the variance exceeds the percentage threshold.","No, because the variance is less than the percentage threshold."],
