    question: "During 2024, Maxwell Corporation engaged in the following transactions:\n\n*   Sold goods to its subsidiary, Sigma Company, for $500,000. Maxwell's cost of goods sold was $300,000. Sigma resold all of the goods to unrelated parties for $650,000.\n*   Leased office space to its majority shareholder, John Smith, for $50,000. The fair rental value of the space is $75,000. John uses the space for personal purposes.\n*   Provided management services to its sister company, Theta Inc., for $100,000. Maxwell's direct costs associated with these services were $60,000. Theta's market research indicated that similar services could have been obtained from an unrelated party for $120,000.\n\nWhat amount should Maxwell Corporation disclose as related party transactions in its 2024 financial statements?",
    options: ["$650,000","$500,000","$670,000","$150,000"],
