    explanation: "The correct answer is C. ASC 850-10-50-1 states that related party relationships exist when one party has the ability to control or significantly influence the other. Transactions between an entity and its management or their immediate family members are considered related party transactions. Since the lease terms are significantly more favorable than market rates, this indicates a potential influence by the CEO's spouse, necessitating disclosure.",
