    options: ["Dixon is required to disclose that substantial doubt exists about its ability to continue as a going concern and disclose management's plan to mitigate the going concern uncertainty if it is probable that the plan will be implemented and alleviate the going concern doubt.","Dixon is required to disclose that substantial doubt exists about its ability to continue as a going concern, but is not required to disclose management's plan to mitigate the going concern uncertainty since the auditor has already raised the issue.","Dixon is required to disclose that substantial doubt exists about its ability to continue as a going concern and disclose management's plan to mitigate the going concern uncertainty regardless of whether the plan is probable of being implemented and alleviating the going concern doubt.","Dixon is not required to disclose any information about the going concern issue if management believes the plan will be successful in the long term."],
