    question: "Which of the following situations would require disclosure as a related party transaction in the financial statements of ABC Company?",
    options: ["ABC Company purchases raw materials from XYZ Corporation. XYZ Corporation accounts for 5% of ABC Company's total raw material purchases, and ABC Company's CEO's brother owns 2% of XYZ Corporation.","ABC Company leases office space from a building owned by the spouse of a member of ABC Company's board of directors. The lease is at market rates and represents an immaterial amount to ABC Company.","ABC Company sells goods to DEF Company, a major customer accounting for 25% of ABC Company's annual revenue. There is no other relationship between ABC Company and DEF Company.","ABC Company provides consulting services to GHI Company. GHI Company is controlled by ABC Company's chief operating officer's (COO) adult daughter."],
    correctAnswer: 3,
    explanation: "Disclosure is required when the reporting entity's chief operating officer's (COO) adult daughter controls GHI Company, and ABC Company provides consulting services to GHI company. The COO is considered a related party to ABC Company, and his daughter's control of GHI Company makes GHI Company a related party as well. Transactions between related parties require disclosure (ASC 850-10-50-1).",
