    subtopic: "Segment Reporting",
    difficulty: "medium",
    skillLevel: "Application",
    question: "ABC Corp. operates in four different industries: Retail Sales, Manufacturing, Financial Services, and Technology. For the year ended December 31, 2023, the following information is available:\n\n| Segment           | Revenue (Millions) | Operating Profit (Millions) | Identifiable Assets (Millions) |\n|-------------------|--------------------|-------------------------------|--------------------------------|\n| Retail Sales      | $150               | $20                           | $100                           |\n| Manufacturing     | $80                | $10                           | $60                            |\n| Financial Services | $220               | $30                           | $150                           |\n| Technology        | $50                | $5                            | $40                            |\n| Total             | $500               | $65                           | $350                           |\n\nBased on ASC 280, which segment(s) are reportable based on the revenue test?",
    options: ["Retail Sales and Financial Services only.","Retail Sales, Manufacturing, and Financial Services only.","Retail Sales, Financial Services, and Technology only.","Retail Sales, Manufacturing, Financial Services, and Technology."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
