    question: "A U.S. based public company, Beta Corp, has the following operating segments: Alpha, Beta, Gamma, and Delta. For the year ended December 31, 2024, these segments had revenues of $50 million, $30 million, $15 million, and $5 million, respectively. Total consolidated revenue for Beta Corp. was $100 million. In addition to these segments, Beta Corp has corporate overhead costs that are not allocated to the operating segments. Which of the following statements is correct regarding reportable segments for Beta Corp. based on the revenue test?",
