    question: "Watson Corp., a U.S.-based company, anticipates purchasing equipment from a vendor in Euros (€) three months from now. To hedge the foreign currency risk, Watson enters into a forward contract to purchase Euros. Watson designates this forward contract as a cash flow hedge. At the end of the first month, the forward contract has a gain of $50,000. Where should Watson report this gain in its financial statements?",
    options: ["Other comprehensive income (OCI)","Current earnings as part of net income","Deferred revenue","As an adjustment to the basis of the equipment when purchased"],
    correctAnswer: 0,
    explanation: "The gain on the forward contract, which is designated as a cash flow hedge, should be reported in other comprehensive income (OCI). The amounts in OCI will be reclassified into earnings in the same period or periods during which the hedged transaction affects earnings (when the equipment is purchased and depreciated). (ASC 815-30-25)",
