    question: "Apex Corp. operates in three reportable segments: Alpha, Beta, and Gamma. Alpha had revenue of $30 million and operating profit of $6 million. Beta had revenue of $25 million and operating profit of $4 million. Gamma had revenue of $20 million and an operating loss of $2 million. Apex also has corporate overhead (not allocated to segments) of $3 million. For the year ended December 31, 2023, what is the amount of consolidated operating profit/loss that Apex Corp. should report, and how is the reportable segment(s) profitability threshold determined?",
