    question: "A publicly traded company, Gamma Corp, operates in three reportable segments: Alpha, Beta, and Delta. For the year ended December 31, 2023, Gamma Corp's consolidated revenue was $50 million. Alpha's revenue was $20 million, Beta's revenue was $16 million, and Delta's revenue was $4 million. Other segments' combined revenue was $10 million. Which of the following statements is correct regarding Gamma Corp's segment reporting requirements?",
    options: ["All three segments (Alpha, Beta, and Delta) are reportable segments because their combined revenue exceeds 75% of the consolidated revenue.","Only Alpha and Beta are reportable segments because they each exceed the 10% revenue threshold of the consolidated revenue.","Only Alpha is a reportable segment because it is the only segment exceeding 20% of the consolidated revenue.","Alpha, Beta, and the combined 'Other segments' are reportable segments because their combined revenue exceeds 75% of the consolidated revenue."],
