    question: "After the balance sheet date of December 31, Year 1, but before the financial statements were issued, Omega Corp. settled a lawsuit for $500,000 related to a product liability claim. The event that gave rise to the lawsuit occurred in Year 1. Omega had previously accrued $200,000 related to this lawsuit. What is the appropriate accounting treatment for this subsequent event?",
    options: ["Adjust the Year 1 financial statements by increasing the accrual by $300,000 and disclose the event in the notes to the financial statements.","Disclose the event in the notes to the financial statements only.","No adjustment or disclosure is required because the event occurred after the balance sheet date.","Adjust the Year 1 financial statements by increasing the accrual by $500,000 and disclose the event in the notes to the financial statements."],
    correctAnswer: 0,
