    educational: "Subsequent events are events occurring between the balance sheet date and the date the financial statements are issued or are available to be issued. Type I events provide additional evidence about conditions that existed at the balance sheet date and require adjustment. Type II events relate to conditions that did not exist at the balance sheet date and generally require disclosure only.",
    examTip: "Pay close attention to the timing of the event that gave rise to the subsequent event. If it occurred before the balance sheet date, it's likely a Type I event requiring adjustment. If it occurred after, it's likely a Type II event requiring disclosure only.",
