    explanation: "The number of software developers hired is a leading indicator because it predicts future capacity and potential revenue. The total contract value of platform subscriptions is a lagging indicator because it reflects the revenue generated after the platform is launched and sold to customers. This directly aligns with the COSO framework's emphasis on forward-looking and retrospective performance measures.",
